<body>
  <h1>Update Notes - v1.1.1 Beta</h1>

  <h2>New</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Added <code>&lt;local&gt;</code> placeholder that returns the local player (the user who clicked the Truth or Dare button).</li>
    <li>Added <code>&lt;range[1-2]&gt;</code> placeholder that generates a positive number within the given range (max: 500).</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="critical">
    <strong>CRITICAL BUG:</strong> If you click the button before it says "Ready!" you may need to create a new instance.
    This will be fixed before the final release.
  </div>

  <p><strong>Note:</strong> It should show "Ready!" on screen when the game is initialized and playable.</p>

  <h2>Changed</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Modified <code>&lt;player&gt;</code> functionality: now uses <code>&lt;player=X&gt;</code> (X = 1–5). Up to five players are supported.</li>
    <ul>
      <li>Example: <code>&lt;local&gt;</code> do you have a crush on any of these players: <code>&lt;player=1&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;player=2&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;player=3&gt;</code></li>
    </ul>
    <li>Increased download rate limit: 10 → 15 seconds.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Fixes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Fixed a second <code>RequestSerialization</code> call that was unnecessary.</li>
    <li>Fixed critical bug where clicking the Truth or Dare button before "Ready!" broke the game.</li>
    <li>Resolved issue with <code>GetAllPlayers</code> not correctly populating the local player array.</li>
    <li>Fixed placeholder handling: unused ones like <code>&lt;player=5&gt;</code> are now removed if not enough players.</li>
    <li>Corrected range input to ensure it stays within 1–500.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Removed</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Removed Player Truths & Player Dares.</li>
    <li>Removed <code>SetQuestion()</code> and <code>Chance()</code>.</li>
    <li>Removed <code>usePlaceholders</code> setting — placeholders are now always enabled by default.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Additional Notes (v1.1.1 Beta)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Includes all fixes from v1.1 release.</li>
    <li>Fixed compatibility issue with Gumroad.</li>
  </ul>
</body>
